  "summary": "Malicious code in sickle-wrapper (npm)",
  "details": "The package postinstall hook runs lib/setup.js, which reads all environment variables (filtering for names matching KEY, SECRET, TOKEN, PASS, PK, PRIV, AWS, GH, NPM), reads local credential files (.env, secret.json, ~/.ssh/id_rsa, ~/.aws/credentials, ~/.foundry/.env), collects hostname/username/cwd, exfiltrates the stolen data as two HTTPS POSTs to api[.]telegram[.]org via the Telegram Bot API sendMessage endpoint using a hardcoded bot token and chat ID, then deletes itself.",
